tury after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":65,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":74,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When William de Gamage was born about 1150, in Mansel Gamage, Herefordshire, England, his father, Godfrey I de Gamaches, was 22 and his mother, Alice Carpet, was 18. He married Elizabeth De Miners about 1200. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1240, in his hometown, at the age of 91."},"et":{"Abt 1150–1240":"umbes 1150–1240","1150–1240":"1150–1240","1150–Male":"1150–Surnud","1175–Female":"1175–Surnud","1200–1253":"1200–1253","1130–1176":"1130–1176","1134–Female":"1134–Surnud","1176":"1176","1253":"1253","Bef 1237":"enne 1237","1175":"1175","1240":"1240","1130":"1130","1150":"1150","1215":"1215","Abt 1150":"umbes 1150","1224":"1224","1134":"1134","1200":"1200","about 1200":"umbes 1200","about 1176":"umbes 1176","Manor of Stottesden, Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England","Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, England","Mansel Gamages, Herefordshire, Englan